SIMPLE: microcosmical
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Microcosmical
<hw>Mi`cro*cos"mic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>microcosmique</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the
microcosm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Microcosmic salt</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>, <cd>a
white crystalline substance obtained by mixing solutions of sodium
phosphate and ammonium phosphate, and also called
<altname>hydric-sodic-ammonic-phosphate</altname>. It is a powerful
flux, and is used as a substitute for borax as a blowpipe reagent in
testing for the metallic oxides. Originally obtained by the alchemists
from human urine, and called <altname>sal
microcosmicum</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Microcosmography</ent>⟦br⟧
